x4freetext: Silicon detectors calibrated using a 232Th alpha
source.
NaI detectors calibrated using a ch target and
observing scattered deuterons from 12C and recoil
protons.
Spectra corrected for:
. reaction tails produced in detector,
. collimator scattering,
. energy loss and straggling in target,
. background arising from target contaminants,
. background contributed from beam.

x4code.headerHelp: Error in value of quantity, defined under ERR-ANALYS

x4freetext: Overall uncertainty, includes contributions
from:
solid angle (~1%),
statistical error (as large as 20% for
high energy tritons, 3He, and alphas),
target thickness (<5%),
integrated beam current (<0.3%),
background from slit scattering (<1%),
uncertainties due to various corrections
VM
DR reference corrected (PR->PR/C)
reactions in subentries 2, 6, 9 , 12 and 15 modified
BP: Corrected ERR-ANALYSIS section.
Corrected reaction codes from deuteron induced to
alpha induced in the existing entries. Digitized all
the curves and updated the compilation.
